To fix the lofree block keyboard on Linux Mint:
1. Open a text editor to create the config file:
    xed ~/.Xmodmap
2. Copy and paste the code block below into that file.
    ! Remap Mac Media Keys to F-Keys for Lofree Block
    ! F1 (Brightness Down) -> F1
    keycode 232 = F1 F1 F1 F1 F1 F1
    ! F2 (Brightness Up) -> F2
    keycode 233 = F2 F2 F2 F2 F2 F2
    ! F3 (Mission Control / Scale) -> F3
    keycode 128 = F3 F3 F3 F3 F3 F3
    ! F4 (Launchpad / Dashboard) -> F4
    keycode 212 = F4 F4 F4 F4 F4 F4
    ! F7 (Rewind) -> F7
    keycode 173 = F7 F7 F7 F7 F7 F7
    ! F8 (Play/Pause) -> F8
    keycode 172 = F8 F8 F8 F8 F8 F8
    !F9 (Fast Forward) -> F9
    keycode 171 = F9 F9 F9 F9 F9 F9
    ! F10 (Mute) -> F10
    keycode 121 = F10 F10 F10 F10 F10 F10
    ! F11 (Volume Down) -> F11
    keycode 122 = F11 F11 F11 F11 F11 F11
    ! F12 (Volume Up) -> F12
    keycode 123 = F12 F12 F12 F12 F12 F12
    ! Remap Print Screen (Fn+F5) to F5
    keycode 107 = F5 F5 F5 F5 F5 F5
    ! Remap Calculator (Fn+F6) to F6
    keycode 148 = F6 F6 F6 F6 F6 F6

Note: since f5 and f6 dont output anything, you have to use fn+f5 and fn+f6 to get them to work. 

Also, you might have to go to settings and unmap the screenshot manually for fn+f5. Go to Start -> keyboard. Click the Shortcuts tab, dropdown system, then "screenshots and recordings". Click "Take a screenshot" and remove the "print" binding by clicking on it and pressing backspace. 

3. Apply the new map by running this command:
    xmodmap ~/.Xmodmap

4. Now to make it permanent. 
    Go to System Setings -> Startup Applications and add a "Custom Command".
Name: LofreeBlock Fix
Command: xmodmap /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.Xmodmap (type whoami in your terminal if you don't know your username)
Comment: Fixes the F Row for the Lofree Block Keyboard
